com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/perception-of-nature-and-environment-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/perception-of-nature-and-environment-in-turkiye.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","caption":"Turkish forest conservation and nature respect","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/perception-of-nature-environment-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/perception-of-nature-environment-in-turkey/","name":"Perception of Nature and Environment in Turkey","datePublished":"2026-01-30T16:34:53+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:39:18+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/perception-of-nature-and-environment-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Perception of Nature and Environment in Turkey","keywords":"Nature","datePublished":"2026-01-30T16:34:53+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:39:18+03:00","articleSection":"Cultural Adaptation","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover the perception of nature and the environment in Turkey. Read our article to raise your awareness and develop your environmental awareness!","name":"Perception of Nature and Environment in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/perception-of-nature-environment-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/perception-of-nature-environment-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/perception-of-nature-and-environment-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/perception-of-nature-environment-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country that attracts attention with its natural beauties as well as its historical and cultural richness. The perception of nature and the environment is an important part of Turkish culture. In this article, we will discuss the value given to nature in Turkish culture, environmental awareness in Turkey and the role of young people in this regard, as well as activities that are intertwined with nature. Ready when you are!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-value-given-to-nature-in-turkish-culture-a-reflections">The Value Given to Nature in Turkish Culture: A Reflections</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkish culture is rooted in a deep respect and devotion to nature. This ancient relationship makes itself felt in a wide range of areas, from mythology to daily life, from art to social values.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkish mythology and folk narratives, nature is not only a place but also a sacred entity, a guide and a source of inspiration. In ancient belief systems, every mountain, tree and spring was considered to have a spirit and these spirits were respected. This understanding made protecting nature and living in harmony with it a philosophy of life. This philosophy is one of the cornerstones of Turkish art and music. Folk songs liken love to the voice of a nightingale, longing to the back of a mountain, and longing to flowing water. In miniatures and carpet patterns, flowers, trees and animals are depicted as part of the endless cycle of nature.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This cultural heritage is also reflected in daily life practices. Life in the countryside is still shaped by the cycles of nature; the awakening of the soil heralds planting time and the cessation of rains heralds the harvest. Traditional agriculture and animal husbandry methods are passed down from generation to generation with a sustainable approach that respects the balance of nature.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="environmental-awareness-in-turkey-the-role-and-contributions-of-young-people">Environmental Awareness in Turkey: The Role and Contributions of Young People</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, environmental awareness has been increasing in Turkey. Young people, in particular, show sensitivity to environmental issues and take an active role in various campaigns and projects. For example, environmental clubs and societies at many universities organize environmental protection activities and raise awareness.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Youth contributions include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Cleaning Campaigns:</strong> Young volunteers carry out regular clean-ups in many locations, from beaches to national parks, from urban recreation areas to river banks. These activities are not limited to the collection of waste, but also aim to draw attention to the source of environmental pollution and raise awareness among individuals. Thanks to the effective use of social media, these movements can reach a wider audience and set an example.</li>



<li><strong>Tree Planting and Nature Revitalization Efforts:</strong> As part of the fight against climate change and deforestation, tree planting activities organized by young people are carried out in cooperation with both local authorities and civil society organizations. These activities contribute to the restoration of degraded ecosystems, while at the same time instilling in participants a love and responsibility for nature.</li>



<li><strong>Environmental Education and Awareness Raising Activities:</strong> Young people aim to raise awareness through educational workshops, seminars and workshops they organize in schools and neighborhoods. Content on topics such as recycling, water conservation and climate-friendly living habits are especially effective on children and young people. In addition, informative posts produced on digital platforms serve to strengthen environmental literacy by reaching large masses.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Such activities not only increase the environmental awareness of young people, but also raise awareness in society.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="nature-with-cultural-experiences-activities-you-can-do-in-turkey">Nature with Cultural Experiences: Activities You Can Do in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey hosts many activities with its natural beauties and rich cultural heritage. Here are some activities where you can get in touch with nature:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Nature Walks:</strong> In many parts of Turkey, especially in mountainous areas, there are wonderful trails where you can go hiking. For example, the Kaz Mountains and Cappadocia are ideal places for nature lovers.</li>



<li><strong>Camping:</strong> You can enjoy nature by camping in various regions of Turkey. Especially holiday resorts such as Fethiye, Bodrum and Antalya are famous for their campsites.</li>



<li><strong>Water Sports:</strong> Turkey&#8217;s unique beaches offer the perfect environment for water sports. Activities such as diving, surfing and canoeing can be intertwined with the sea and nature.</li>



<li><strong>Cultural Tours:</strong> In addition to nature, you can join tours organized to explore historical and cultural riches. For example, places like the ancient city of Ephesus and Pamukkale are of interest for both nature and history lovers.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="are-you-ready-to-discover-turkeys-natural-beauties">Are You Ready to Discover Turkey&#8217;s Natural Beauties?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers a unique experience for international students and visitors with its natural beauty and cultural richness. The value placed on nature in Turkish culture, environmental awareness and the contributions of young people demonstrate this country&#8217;s respect for nature. Activities intertwined with nature offer both a fun and educational experience. If you are thinking of studying or living in Turkey, you can make unforgettable memories by taking advantage of these opportunities.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-environmental-awareness-high-in-turkey">Is environmental awareness high in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Individual sensitivity is high, but systemic and political responses are insufficient.</p>


<h3 class="ds-markdown-paragraph">What shapes the view of environmental problems?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Economic concerns, cultural heritage, media influence, and youth activism are some of the most important factors influencing the perspective on environmental issues.</p>


<h3 class="ds-markdown-paragraph">What are the most important environmental concerns?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Air pollution, water scarcity, waste management and deforestation top the list of environmental concerns.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-social-media-affects-environmental-perception">How social media affects environmental perception?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It raises awareness but may be limited to short-term reactions.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-there-hope-for-the-future">Is there hope for the future?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The rising environmental movement, especially among the younger generation and civil society, is promising.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are considering studying abroad, Turkey offers many opportunities. Don&#8217;t miss this unique experience to give your education a new direction!</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-01-30T13:34:53Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:39:18Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/perception-of-nature-and-environment-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Turkish forest conservation and nature respect","title":"perception-of-nature-and-environment-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'perception-of-nature-environment-in-turkey' );
